commit 8fd6c0c231a6ffc3504a1031822f4149b6518228
Author: roopak <roopak.houji@truminds.com>
Date:   Wed Apr 8 15:05:24 2026 +0530

    Fix for nndpi_train.py
    Change 1 — Fix Input Shape Tuple
    In Python, (max_len) is not a tuple — it is just max_len wrapped in parentheses (just grouping, no tuple created).
    max_len = 100
    
    (max_len)    # this is just 100 — NOT a tuple
    (max_len,)   # this is (100,) — a proper 1D tuple
    
    Keras Input(shape=...) expects a tuple. Without the trailing comma, it receives an integer instead of a tuple, causing an error
    Adding the comma , makes it a proper 1D tuple (100,) — telling Keras the input is a 1D array of length max_len
    
    Change 2 — Add Classification Tag Parameters
    The original model had hardcoded output class counts inside the function. This change makes them configurable parameters with default values.
    
    out1 = Dense(4, activation='softmax')(x)   # 4 classes — hardcoded
    out2 = Dense(8, activation='softmax')(x)   # 8 classes — hardcoded
    out3 = Dense(9, activation='softmax')(x)   # 9 classes — hardcoded
    out4 = Dense(6, activation='softmax')(x)   # 6 classes — hardcoded
    
    out1 = Dense(n_tag_1, activation='softmax')(x)   # configurable
    out2 = Dense(n_tag_2, activation='softmax')(x)   # configurable
    out3 = Dense(n_tag_3, activation='softmax')(x)   # configurable
    out4 = Dense(n_tag_4, activation='softmax')(x)   # configurable

