commit 999104d6302262934b1cd70612ed64eecb3244bf (HEAD -> main)
Author: roopak <roopak.houji@truminds.com>
Date:   Wed Apr 8 15:19:14 2026 +0530

    Included inference file for PC
    What the Inference Script Does
    In machine learning, "inference" is the phase where you take a fully trained AI and ask it to evaluate brand-new data it has never seen before. Specifically, your script does the following:
    
    Loads the AI's "Brain": It builds the neural network structure and loads the pre-trained weights (from the ./Model/nndpi.h5 file). This file contains all the patterns the AI learned during its training phase.
    
    Reads Your Network Traffic: It opens the .feather files inside your ./ProcessedPackets/ folder.
    
    Strips the Cheatsheet: It removes any metadata (like filenames or existing tags) from the packets. It forces the AI to look only at the raw payload bytes (columns 0 through 1499).
    
    Makes Predictions: It feeds those raw bytes into the neural network. The network calculates the mathematical probability of what kind of traffic that packet belongs to.
    
    Picks the Winner: For each of the 4 categories (Tags), it finds the class with the highest probability (using np.argmax) and translates that back into a readable result.

